Frank Turner - England Keep My Bones (2011)(Deluxe Edition / 3 Bonus Tracks(FLAC)









Frank Turner (born 28 December 1981) is an English folk/punk singer-songwriter from Meonstoke, Winchester, who was born in Manama, Bahrain. Initially the vocalist of post-hardcore band Million Dead, Turner embarked upon a primarily acoustic-based solo career following the band's split in 2005. To date, Turner has released four solo albums, a rarities compilation album and four EPs. Turner began recording for his new album &quot;England Keep My Bones&quot;, in January 2011. It was released on June 6, 2011 in the UK, and June 7, 2011 worldwide.
